<concept_spec>

concept Scene

purpose 
    to manage the three.js rendering scene, camera, and visual objects

state
    a Scene with
        a backgroundColor Number
        a ambientIntensity Number
        a directionalIntensity Number
    a Camera with
        a position Vector3
        a target Vector3
        a fov Number
    a set of Meshes with
        a geometry String
        a material String
        a position Vector3
        a rotation Quaternion
        a vertices Array
    a set of Lights with
        a type String
        a color Number
        a intensity Number
        a position Vector3

actions
    initialize (width: Number, height: Number) : (scene: Scene, camera: Camera)
        create three.js scene and renderer
        setup camera with perspective projection
        configure rendering settings
        return scene and camera references
    
    addLight (light: Lights, type: String, color: Number, intensity: Number, position: Vector3) : (light: Lights)
        create light of specified type
        add to scene
        return light reference
    
    createMesh (mesh: Meshes, geometry: String, material: String, position: Vector3) : (mesh: Meshes)
        create mesh with geometry and material
        set initial position
        add to scene
        return mesh reference
    
    updateMesh (mesh: Meshes, vertices: Array) : (mesh: Meshes)
        update mesh vertex positions
        mark geometry for update
        return mesh reference
    
    removeMesh (mesh: Meshes) : ()
        remove mesh from scene
    
    render () : (scene: Scene)
        render current frame
        return scene reference
    
    setCameraPosition (camera: Camera, position: Vector3, target: Vector3) : (camera: Camera)
        update camera position and look-at target
        return camera reference
    
    resize (width: Number, height: Number) : (scene: Scene)
        update renderer size
        adjust camera aspect ratio
        return scene reference

operational principle
    after initialize (width: 800, height: 600) : (scene: s, camera: c)
    and addLight (type: "ambient", intensity: 0.5) : (light: l1)
    and createMesh (geometry: "sphere", material: "standard", position: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0}) : (mesh: m)
    and render ()
    a sphere is visible in the rendered scene

</concept_spec>
